entries.femaleVariant: To grab the tech Songbird and I both need, we gotta go to a meet with Hansen. Prep for it's required.
Personality imprint theft... Sounds like our Colombian job of yore. Who are they and where do we find 'em?
[Sit] Spoke with So Mi.
I know your friend Reed is FIA. My natural assumpton is – you're an agent, too.
I’m also guessing you two took it upon yourselves to save the president, then exfil her out of Dogtown.
Cracked the case. Smart man.
Don't scare that easily.
Wow, you cracked it. Clever man.
To be honest, I got tired of the media circus. All the allegations thrown in my face, the bullshit propaganda…
You tryin' to scare me?
Dunno. Are you afraid?
Your little bird came to me on her own, though. She was tired of breaking international laws on the president’s whim. She simply had to run away.
Haul ass outta there.
Sheesh, colossal prick… Hear what he said?
Yeah, caught it all.
Hansen.
Songbird.
Hansen.
Yes... but not really.
Thinkin' Songbird planned the whole thing.
[Join game] Bettin' on red.
[Stand] Let’s get to it.
Will you join us?
What, no introduction?
Place your bets, please.
Man’s a career criminal.
Ain’t no upstanding citizen, that’s sure.
Sister’s right.
Owning Dogtown’s one helluva bargaining tool.
He’s a famed, top-tier pro criminal. Can't just don a suit, stroll into the relevant city agency and register Hansen, Incorporated.
Still no sign from Reed, V... Got a sinkin' feelin' about this.
Certainly not liable to become a tax-payin', law-abidin' Night Citizen.
[Bet on red]
[Bet on black]
Red.
Black.
Reed’s still not responding. But you keep workin' it. Let's go, swap twins.
Sister’s right, ya know. Legit biz – lots better, safer than the gangster shit.
Man basically owns Dogtown. Could use that as leverage.
To be upstanding in the eyes of others – I could not give a shit.
Got a bad feelin' about this... C'mon, shake 'im, head for the exit.
[Walk away] Now what?
[Walk away] Hear what he said?
Greetings, madam.
[Exchange money] Need some chips.
Who’d that be?
What're you thinkin'?
[Give shard] Our targets – redheaded twins.
So, how's one go about it – kleppin' someone's personality.
Song got this shard to me – take a look. Our targets are a brother and sister, red-haired twins. They're here somewhere, schmoozing.
FIA metanthropic tech – Alex has access, you’ve seen her use it already. You look, sound and act like the individual whose personality you assume.
To do it, we need scans of our targets.
Twin roulette, looks like…
Hmm… OK, we need to pull data, get samples of assorted behavior. We make contact with 'em, talk, scan as we talk.
Wanna buy some chips.
Of course. Good luck at the tables.
All bets are in. Betting is closed.
Wears many masks, this one. Give her a good shake, she might shed one or two.
Oh, don’t be silly. His real name would appear nowhere on the documents.
Kickbacks to NC officials – are they not taxes, not protection money? Doing business carries a price.
I myself have a small firm in Paris. My stand-in take calls, arranges meetings and deflects, deflects, deflects.
Do something, anything to get more than one sentence outta this wannabe mime.
Ah, please… What would he do? Build homes, strip malls?
Right. Back to the sitch at hand. What do we have to do to save 'er?
All good there, Reed?
Yeah. I just need to process for a minute. It's just how I'm built. A little adversity, and I need a few moments to think.
Yeah. We now know who took a swipe at Myers' head.
Talked to Songbird via the Relic. We can communicate again.
Read you loud and clear. Preppin' scan tech now.
V, zippin' funds your way from our operating budget. Load up on chips and join their game. Just don’t go all-in from the get-go.
You're new to this, but relax. We'll do it as a four-hander – I scan one, you handle the other. Alex'll pilot us through.
Relax, buy 'em drinks, break the ice. I'll join you momentarily.
You heard the lady. And Real Water for the gentleman here.
How about we go all-in? Bet everything we won tonight.
Red.
Black.
I'm seein' red comin'…
Black's my choice.
And what'll you have?
Over there.
Alex, you copy that?
Personality kleppin' – what's that about?
Got it… I think. So, time to make our move?
Betting's open?
Black it is, then.
[Join game] Feelin' lucky about black.
By all means.
Make it red.
V. You?
Aurore Cassel. And that bore is my brother – Aymeric.
What’s your poison? My treat.
<mothertongue l="fra" m="mon frère" b="Bourbon for me. Alas, " a=" does not drink."/>
Why would he need that?
Hansen? Providing weapons to banana republics is not quite a sure and stable business.
[Bet on red]
[Bet on black]
I mean, Hansen could take Dogtown by the throat, eject the junkies and make it a paradise for billionaires.
She’s gettin’ chatty. Doin' good, V.
Soldier yesterday, crime lord today... why not biz shark tomorrow?
Yet he is a businessman.
And to make it legal? It is a lot of work to do for a simple change of label.
Allow me to say, V… arms or property, it would make no difference to me what I sell.
Gimme somethin' big now. Make 'em laugh or cry, I don't care.
All or nothin' – whaddaya say?
Have a taste for risk?
Like the tingle of risk?
<kiroshi l="fra" o="Oh, ma vieille, t'as pas idée…" t="Oh, my dear, you have no idea..." b="" a=""/>
entries.maleVariant: <kiroshi l="fra" o="Oh, mon vieux, t'as pas idée…" t="Oh, my dear, you have no idea..." b="" a=""/>

entries.femaleVariant: Thinkin' we can add a little spice to our game.
I'm listening…
My, my, I, too, am curious…
And we play different colors, yes? You win or we do. And either you or we lose all.
My thoughts exactly.
You choose first, then.
Black for us, then.
We are red, as our hair, a luscious color.
<kiroshi l="fra" o="Putain merde..." t="For fuck's sake…" b="" a=""/>
Congratulation to you.
<kiroshi l="fra" o="Oui!" t="Yes!" b="" a=""/>
It is a nice feeling.
I, too, congratulate you.
Ha, ha, ha... You win some, you lose some, folks.
Leave us for a moment, if you please.
We're just talking, aren't we.
I will let you and Reed walk free of this place, in one piece, on your own two feet. Consider it a gesture of my good will.
I’ve matters to attend to. You'll find Mr. Reed downstairs.
We stagger our approach. And we're strangers.
Same as the lady.
Same as the lady.
Your drinks will be here shortly.
Same as the gentleman.
Whiskey.
Gin 'n' tonic.
Same as the gentleman.
Hard liquor, please... Whiskey?
G 'n' T, please.
Bourbon. Comin' up.
Water. Comin' right up.
Inori OK with you?
Japanese, more'n fine.
Gin, tonic, be right back.
Hmm, I just realized… you must have dirt beneath your fingernails, too. Like all these bastards and bitches.
<mothertongue l="fra" m="une touriste" b="That is, unless you’re " a=". Like the no-lifers who must watch others live to feel anything."/>
entries.maleVariant: <mothertongue l="fra" m="un touriste" b="That is, unless you’re " a=". Like the no-lifers who must watch others live to feel anything."/>

entries.femaleVariant: Tourist – that's me.
Got me. No-lifer, tourist, whatever your preference.
Hmm... You’re just teasing.
Conscience ain't spotless, that's sure.
Yeah, conscience ain't sparklin' clean, no.
I like those who brag about such things.
Whaddaya think I am?
My, my! One drink and already flirting? Bold.
Guess.
<mothertongue l="fra" m="monsieur" b="We were discussing local politics. Specifically our host, " a=" Kurt Hansen."/>
Big fish, selling big guns for big money. Yet here… you have celebrities, politicians, even the chief of police…
<mothertongue l="fra" m="véritable" b="So I was thinking... Perhaps Hansen would do better by being a " a=" businessman, no?"/>
<mothertongue l="fra" m="Mon cher frère" b="I claim he would. " a=" disagrees."/>
Just getting rich is dull. You should work for the community… invest, create jobs, throw banquets…
You’re so childish it’s beautiful.
What?
And who would Hansen be? The mayor? Please…
He is very good at what he does. A professional criminal.
And to spend five years on efforts to… change how people see you, call you?
You know, V – just go big… like, humongous. Provoke 'em.
Pass it on to President Myers. Also, tell her... her toy of mass destruction is my friend now. And she should get the fuck out of my back yard, or the world will learn about her games.
Didn't like it one bit, either.
Stall for time, OK?
Psychoanalysis – hobby of yours?
The fuck? Psychoanalysis a hobby 'o yours?
<mothertongue l="fra" m="Non, putain..." b="" a=" I’m merely trying to have a conversation."/>
I'm asking what you think of him, not if his parents loved him.
V, no! Too hard!
Businessman, through and through.
Hansen’s a suit without a suit, if you catch my drift.
Oh my fucking God, you Americans... You used to have more imagination.
Tossin' you around, V, don't let 'er. Level the field.
Ask a gonk question, get a gonk answer. Deservedly, I'd say.
Dumb question, dumb answer.
How 'bout you tell us what's bouncin' 'round your noggin?
<mothertongue l="fra" m="Touché." b="" a=""/>
Maybe you could lay out your opinion of the man?
<mothertongue l="fra" m="Profiter de la vie" b="" a=", to enjoy life – that is the point. You can wage wars to make money, but why do so at all if you must then hide it?"/>
Aymeric knows this, I know this... and if Hansen has any sense, he knows it, too.
Guy's a warlord with a huge ego.
Conqueror, that's his mentality.
Seem a lot alike, you 'n' Hansen. Never a step back, always leapin' forward. And you love the fuck outta this work.
<mothertongue l="fra" m="Ben, putain" b="" a=", now you do the <Rich color=\"MainColors.ActiveBlue\">psychanalyse</>?"/>
Playin' your own game, Aurore.
<kiroshi l="fra" o="Santé, V." t="Cheers, V." b="" a=""/>
Guy's a warlord with an oversized ego. Just look at the state of Dogtown.
Thank you for the bourbon, V.
Ugh. You botched that... can’t get ahold of Reed, classic MIA... nothing’s goin' right.
And charities are excellent washing machines, you launder billions. Believe me.
Makes more sense for him to retire, not go legit.
Naive and shortsighted, your approach.
If I was him, I'd liquidate. Head from some tropical exile, spend the rest of my days drinkin' gaudy, candy-ass cocktails.
Naive thinkin', friend. You wearin' digiblinders…?
Thinks you're a dolt, V. Readin's useless, do somethin' else!
Hansen could make a deal, no doubt about it.
M I hearin' your ego talkin'?
Got it right and you know that. Your ego just won't let you admit it.
Of course.
He's withdrawing and we still need a strong response from him! Lemme think real quick...
'Course, ain't about holin' up on a yacht, waitin' for hitmen to show up.
But he could make a deal. Appoint a successor or offer a generous pay-off.
The question remains – what for?
For fuck’s sake, V!
Excuse me?
No offense, but... you're claimin' there's no point in Hansen goin' legal. He's makin' great scratch as a criminal.
Yes, and...?
Wow. Just opened him up. Nice.
Go on, choose.
Gettin' there, almost got it.
Far from perfect, but slowly, slowly... we'll get there.
Not doin' great, V. Got an idea, though.
V... Can't get ahold of Reed. No idea where he is.
Hansen going missionary position in business? Nonsense.
A man like Hansen cannot retire. His partners in business would not allow it. Community, you see.
Mhm…
Struck gold with roulette, really. Gambling throws people around, high and low, brings the joy of winning and the despair of defeat. Perfect for our purposes.
Let’s get to this.
[Order drinks] What’s your poison?
How's things? Any luck?
We started just moments ago.
Listen. Reed's MIA for now, can't wait for 'im. Gotta do both scans on your own.
Delicious drink, V, thank you.
Whaddaya mean?
They would hunt him, find him, put a bag over his head and bring him back. If he said "no," he would die. There is simply too much money involved.
Meanin', sure, he can stay in his comfort zone, churn out eddies. Or… with a bit of legwork, become an untouchable gazillionaire.
Tons of hustlers, plain criminals out there donned suits. Fuckers are truly above the law now.
<mothertongue l="fra" m="Une diversification" b="Dogtown needs Night City to prosper. Hansen needs it. " a=" of profit centers makes sense."/>
Now that is some cheap psychoanalytic bullshit.
Wanted an answer – you got it.
Can't say I know him all that well.
Don’t know the guy that well, really.
Honest. I like it. Better this than invented nonsense.
<mothertongue l="fra" m="diversifier" b="Empty banter aside, a stupid man the colonel is not. He should... " a=" revenues and assets."/>
OK, V. Got all we need.
Need an array of emotions, so provoke. But subtly so, or they'll clam up, scan'll be a bust.
How's it going?
OK, whadda I do now?
V – important. You’re not there to have fun. Simple bets, red or black only. None of the Double Street or Basket bullshit, understood?
One, odd, red.
Two, even, black.
Three, odd, red.
Four, even, black.
Five, odd, red.
Six, even, black.
Seven, odd, red.
Eight, even, black.
Nine, odd, red.
Ten, even, black.
Eleven, odd, black.
Twelve, even, red.
Thirteen, odd, black.
Fourteen, even, red.
Fifteen, odd, black.
Sixteen, even, red.
Seventeen, odd, black.
Eighteen, even, red.
Nineteen, odd, red.
Twenty, even, black.
Twenty-one, odd, red.
Twenty-two, even, black.
Twenty-three, odd, red.
Twenty-four, even, black.
Twenty-five, odd, red.
Twenty-six, even, black.
Twenty-seven, odd, red.
Twenty-eight, even, black.
Twenty-nine, odd, black.
Thirty, even, red.
Thirty-one, odd, black.
Thirty-two, even, red.
Thirty-three, odd, black.
Thirty-four, even, red.
Thirty-five, odd, black.
Thirty-six, even, red.
Zero.
Come up with anything?
Dunno about you, but I see coincidences as patterns, structures we have yet to recognize.
Cause we show up as a pair of 'runners. Need to “klep their identities” first, whatever that means…
I should send you back to Night City in body bags filled with pieces.
Luckily, we can put all that behind us now.
Brave face you’re puttin' on…
Always willin' to help.
What else you got to say?
Oh, so you coudn't be happier we saved Myers after your botched hit? Riiight. Think you believe that less than I do.
Always willin' to help. Don't you worry, got your back, Colonel.
Oh... So what now? Gonna kidnap me? Torture me?
entries.maleVariant: So what now? Gonna kidnap me? Torture me?

entries.femaleVariant: Breaching the Blackwall? Jeopardizing the Net, all humankind's safety, in fact, for personal gain? I wonder what NetWatch would say…
So, gonna rescue a traitor?
How you feelin' about this?
Right. Just branded your beloved belle of the ball who you're out to rescue a traitor. What now? What do you wanna do about it?
So, what're you thinkin' about all this?
You're thinkin' right.
Hm. Whatcha drivin' at?
SF1 crashes. Not anywhere, but over specific turf. Controlled by someone who found some obscure, forgotten tech in a secret bunker.
Right…
Crash was an inside job, we suspected that from the get-go.
You know, V, treason ain't ever black and white. They tried to zero me once, too... What if we’ve all been played?
I’m not convinced So Mi's to blame for everything. In this trade, nothing's ever as it seems. You gotta keep askin' questions till you get to the bottom of it. That's experience talkin'.
Fuck! Hansen’s comin'...
Easy, V. No tension, make sure he thinks all’s preem.
Scan 'em now. It's why you went there!
<kiroshi l="fra" o="Eh bah voilà, c'est comme ça qu'on fait !" t="That’s the way to do it!" b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="fra" o="Ah, putain!" t="Ah, fuck!" b="" a=""/>
Oh, yesss…
<mothertongue l="fra" m="fait chier" b="A defeat, " a="."/>
<kiroshi l="fra" o="Ouais... Par ici l'argent, viens voir maman..." t="Yeah... Come to mommy, crazy money…" b="" a=""/>
Ah, damn... I should have bet on red…
Put it together in a flash.
Not too early for conclusions?
My thoughts exactly.
And it took you just one drink to cobble that together?
Too early for conclusions, don'tcha think? Got no proof she planned this in advance. Coulda improvised, reacted to facts.
Yeah, ‘s what I been thinkin', too. Minute she mentioned the cure, said Hansen has it… Everything just started slidin' into the right boxes, completing the picture.
Started seein' the pieces fallin' into place up on the mezzanine. So Mi told us she’s dyin', things follow from that.
C'mon. You don’t actually think she learned about the cure just now.
Yeah, same here.
Myers pressured So Mi, to reach further, breach boundaries. And then… So Mi snapped.
She made a deal with Hansen earlier, had to, before any of this went down. Traded the president's life for access to the tech.
High treason, no matter how you cut it..
Dunno. Song contacted me with a view to rescuing Myers…
If there's truth to this, Song's guilty of... high treason.
entries.maleVariant: If there's truth to this, Song's guilty of high treason.

entries.femaleVariant: Dunno about that. Song recruited me specifically to pull Myers outta that wreck. Seriuosly doubt she wanted her dead or snatched by Hansen…
Her and her actions I won't judge. Not my place.
It's never that simple, V.
As I see it, So Mi was playin' both sides. Simultaneously spinnin' deals with Hansen and you.

She has Hansen set, then you come in. She contacts you via the Relic, asks you to rescue the president. Absolution for her right there... You need the cure just as much – guaranteein' you'll help if her plan falls through.
And here we are…
Yeah, and here we are – rushin' to Songbird's rescue. Thinkin' a few steps ahead was always her strength. But judgement calls and situational assessment – her Achilles' heel.
As a chess master, she’d be famous for dazzling plays and excruciatingly beautiful defeats.
Gotta believe Song'll keep her word.
Shit, get the impression Song's playin' me…
Sheesh. Not sure what to believe.
Still trust 'er… trust she'll keep her word. Promised me the "cure," an' I fully intend to get it. Only thing that matters, really.
Need to be careful.
Shit, can't shake the feelin' she's still runnin' a game. Sure, seems more upfront than at first. No way she's tellin' all, though.
Sheesh, dunno what to believe just yet...
That's not surprisin'.
Could be right. Stayin' alert's never a bad idea.
I'd be careful. Mind sharp, eyes and ears attuned…
But… I know So Mi well enough to know she'll do her damndest to be fair.
Main thing now is to get her outta this cesspool of a sitch. Then we'll see which direction to take.
Agreed.
Not sure I get you, Reed.
Here to get my due, what i was promised.
Right. Still should watch her every move closely.
Right. No point in porin' over it now.
Still can’t figure you out, Reed. Tryin' to stay true to both the FIA and your friend... Could be recipe for failure.
Just want what Songbird promised me. The "cure," that's it.
Sure. Unconditional trust? No more, out the window.
Yeah. First things first.
Think I don't know that? I wanna gather info, know where I stand before I decide the way forward. Just how I'm built.
Understood. I'll handle the rest, the fallout.
Noticed them some time ago. They stand out even in this melting pot.
Who is Kurt Hansen, really – a crucial question.
Cool!
<kiroshi l="fra" o="Et merde !" t="Shit!" b="" a=""/>
A moment. You join the table, buy drinks, talk and talk… Now you wish to risk everything? I find this disquieting.
Perhaps you could now tell us about yourself.
V, merc from the Afterlife.
I’m a thief.
None of your biz.
FIA agent.

<kiroshi l="fra" o="Nan, mais sérieux ? Juste pour cette fois, fais-moi plaise et arrête d'être méfiant, frangin. S'teuplaît." t="Are you serious? Indulge me this one time and let your guard down, dear brother. Pretty please." b="" a=""/>
Name’s V, Afterlife affiliated. Make what you will of it.
Professional thief, that's who I am. Robbed Yorinobu Arasaka once, figured I'd rob Hansen, too. Or you, for that matter.
None of your biz, choom.
Lookin’ at an FIA operative. That a problem?
Are you happy now?
Isn’t she marvelous?
I agree with V. Let’s play.
Ah, another  game. Let's assume you have not lied. Are you here for Hansen or for us?
Who cares? Let's play.
You're not about to kill us. Got it right?
You won’t send us back in body bags.
Any thoughts?
She'd just... had enough.
What're you thinkin'?
Go on. Spill.
Ah! Fucking done here.
What's your thinkin'?
It's like runnin' along the edge, story of your life, kinda.
Provocative, this one…
Can't help feelin' I, uh, interrupted somethin'… when I walked up.
entries.maleVariant: Can't help feelin' I... interrupted somethin'… when I walked up.

entries.femaleVariant: Do not worry yourself about this.
Real careful, now….
Phew, nice little dodge, V.
<kiroshi l="fra" o="Tu ne serais pas en train de devenir trop pote avec elle ?" t="Not getting a little too damn chummy with her?" b="" a=""/>
entries.maleVariant: <kiroshi l="fra" o="Tu ne serais pas en train de devenir trop pote avec lui ?" t="Not getting a little too damn chummy with him?" b="" a=""/>

entries.femaleVariant: Audacity your callin' card?
Charmin' little show.
<kiroshi l="fra" o="Fais pas ton jaloux, p'tit frère. C'est pas comme si on allait baiser, elle et moi." t="Don't be jealous, little brother. I don't intend to fuck her." b="" a=""/>
entries.maleVariant: <kiroshi l="fra" o="Fais pas ton jaloux, p'tit frère. C'est pas comme si on allait baiser, lui et moi." t="Don't be jealous, little brother. I don't intend to fuck him." b="" a=""/>

entries.femaleVariant: Pretty shameless bastard, aren't you.
Charmin' little show you're puttin' on.
Oh, I agree.
You see, Aymeric, We are charming.
<kiroshi l="fra" o="Elle n'est vraiment pas très fûtée, cette petite." t="The little girl is not terribly sharp." b="" a=""/>
entries.maleVariant: <kiroshi l="fra" o="Il n'est vraiment pas très fûté, ce petit." t="The little boy is not terribly sharp." b="" a=""/>

entries.femaleVariant: <kiroshi l="fra" o="C'est pas comme si je voulais coucher avec elle." t="It's not as if I want to sleep with her." b="" a=""/>
entries.maleVariant: <kiroshi l="fra" o="C'est pas comme si je voulais coucher avec lui." t="It's not as if I want to sleep with him." b="" a=""/>

entries.femaleVariant: V, think I figured 'em out. Little duo's got a habit of testing boundaries, provoking to see what emerges. You gotta play along... to a point.
Good, little worm's openin' up.
Please place your bets.
What do you think? Will you tell?
Care to expand? Floor's yours.
Don't got much respect for upright, honest peeps, do ya.
Tread lightly…
<kiroshi l="fra" o="Allez, allez, allez, allez…" t="C'mon, c'mon, c'mon, c'mon…" b="" a=""/>
[Bet on red] Can tell you got somethin' on the tip of your tongue.
[Bet on black] Guessin' you got no respect for upright, honest peeps.
Oh, come, come. V is just being cordial.
<mothertongue l="fra" m="N'est-ce pas" b="" a=", V? You weren't snooping just now, were you?"/>
Sure wasn't snoopin', no. Just bein' plain courteous.
Oh, don't be such a bore. I simply don't like bores.
Of course you were snooping. As we are simply too interesting to ignore.
Tread carefully with that duo, V...
Ah, ya got me. Onto you big time. But in my defense, you guys stand out, even in a crowd like this one.
entries.maleVariant: Ah, ya got me. Onto you big time. But in my defense, you guys stand out... even in a crowd like this one.

entries.femaleVariant: Oh, really?
Listening to conversations of strangers can be... dangerous. Sometimes, you can hear more than you can handle.
[Bet on red] Didn't mean to be rude, certainly.
[Bet on black] You're unique, stick out from the crowd.
Ugh... Guess it's not my lucky day.
[Drink]
[Bet on red] Seems I interrupted something just now.
[Bet on black] Didn't mean to break your flow.
[Lean]
[Straighten up]
Last chance... Let's go, let's go...
Eight's my magic number. So... Gonna go with eight!
Now we know it was. And we know it was Songbird, she was behind it.
Wow. Traced them in a flash, Reed.
Seems they're playing roulette.
Traced them in no time.
Making some serious accusations here...
The NUS prez, sold to a crime lord... Huge if true.
Understood.
!OBSOLETE
!OBSOLETE
[Exchange chips]
